            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion wedges </strong>and<strong> butternut squash cubes</strong> to a baking tray with<strong> </strong>2/3 of your <strong>ras el hanout </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714666603767-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
